OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,440,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1778328667
OL,3,CEx-prison officer jailed over illicit
OL,4,Ccontact with prisoner and supplying
OL,5,Cdrugs
OL,7,FTwo small mobile phones were later
OL,8,Ffound in the inmate's cell, with
OL,9,Frecords detailing two-way contact with
OL,10,FRichards.
OL,12,FThe South West Regional Organised
OL,13,FCrime Unit (SWROCU) found that
OL,14,FRichards had also been supplying Class
OL,15,FC drug diazepam to associates.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/5
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,440,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1778328667
OL,3,CEx-prison officer jailed over illicit
OL,4,Ccontact with prisoner and supplying
OL,5,Cdrugs
OL,7,FSWROCU Corruption Investigator PC Mark
OL,8,FPaterson said: "Richards would have
OL,9,Fbeen fully aware of her duty to inform
OL,10,Fsupervisors that a serving prisoner
OL,11,Fwas in possession of a mobile phone
OL,12,Fand that she had been having phone
OL,13,Fcontact with him.
OL,15,F"Illicit mobile phones in the hands of
OL,16,Fcriminals allows them the opportunity
OL,17,Fto continue their criminality both
OL,18,Finside the prison and in the community.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,440,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1778328667
OL,3,CEx-prison officer jailed over illicit
OL,4,Ccontact with prisoner and supplying
OL,5,Cdrugs
OL,7,F"Prison staff neglecting their duty by
OL,8,Ffailing to report the existence of
OL,9,Fsuch phones can potentially lead to
OL,10,Ffurther serious crimes being committed
OL,11,Fand leave themselves open to
OL,12,Fmanipulation and blackmail by
OL,13,Fprisoners.
OL,15,F"Richards further offended by
OL,16,Fsupplying controlled drugs outside of
OL,17,Fthe prison estate. Her actions fell
OL,18,Ffar below what would be expected of a
OL,19,Fpublic servant in a position of trust."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/5
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
